content:
When you clone a standard bot as an enhanced bot, the guided cloning experience reconfigures features that work differently for enhanced bots.

To use enhanced Messaging channels with Enhanced Bots, view required editions. Einstein Bots is available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience.

Context Variables
We map the following context variables to their corresponding messaging objects.
CONTEXT VARIABLE	OBJECT	FIELD LABEL	API NAME
Routable Id	Messaging Session	Messaging Session ID	MessagingSession.Id
End User Id	Messaging Session	Messaging User	MessagingSession.MessagingEndUserId
Contact Id	Messaging User	Contact	MessagingEndUser.ContactId

If you don't reference the Chat Key context variable in your dialogs, we delete it from your variables. If you reference the Chat Key variable, we generate a list of affected dialogs.

Conversation Routing
INBOUND: SEND CONVERSATIONS TO YOUR ENHANCED BOT	OUTBOUND: TRANSFER CONVERSATIONS FROM YOUR ENHANCED BOT

When you clone a standard bot as an enhanced bot, we create simple inbound and outbound Omni-Channel flows for your bot. To use these flows:
In Flow Builder, specify a fallback queue in the Route Work action.
Add your flow to a Messaging channel.
Create an inbound or outbound Omni-Channel flow from scratch.

All of your dialogs ending in the Transfer to Agent Next Step are cloned and routed to the default outbound Omni-Channel flow. We revert the Transfer to Agent system dialog to default, so any customizations arenâ€™t cloned.
title: Cloning Service Cloud Bots
